      <hedline>
        <hl1>It's Time to Talk About Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard Joffe letter contends that those who need more evidence of global warming might wait until it is too late to avert catastrophe (Sept 28 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The debate about global warming seems to be between those who believe that there is evidence of such a trend and those who believe that it is too early to tell.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The debate about global warming seems to be between those who believe that there is evidence of such a trend and those who believe that it is too early to tell.</p>
        <p>Those who think that it is too early to tell should consider this: By the time we can expect to be able to tell -- or, rather, by the time we can expect our descendants to be able to tell -- it will be too late to avert catastrophe if indeed the globe is warming because of human activities.</p>
        <p>Other than selfishness, what justification could there be for ignoring the possible danger?</p>
        <p>Richard Joffe  New York, Sept. 28, 2005</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
